{
  "stem": "142.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they had very good relationships, so I think he arranged it to be-- once they were-- it cost nothing to the Greek government.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after returning to Salonika, what were things like when you came back?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I came back, the newspaper didn't exist anymore.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Germans came in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They closed the newspaper.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I-- I was trying to-- to find a job, actually for over-- over a year.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Another Danish cousin, the father had a mill to grind up-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the-- what they call it?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "To make bread, you know, just the-- the wheat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were coming from the-- around-- around Salonika, the people they had wheat, you know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had to mill it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they came down to us and I worked for a year, you know, all night long actually, doing that kind of work.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, that was from 1941 to 1943, when the Germans started surrounding the-- the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For-- at one point, was OK, the first year.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But then I think the Germans started asking a lot of questions, going to the Jewish community and find out who they are.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, they started to have, you know, I think in 1942 the-- what was the-- the head in Germany?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The-- what was the meeting they had for the Final Solution?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Wannsee.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Wannsee.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Wannsee.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after that, you know, they-- they start just going after the Jews of Salonika.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were lots of them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So this is how-- but we went-- we left in 1943.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Italian government put us in an Italian, they call it [ITALIAN], in an Italian-- the-- they were coming to Salonika, railroads from Italy, and they took us to the Italian part of Greece.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
